556
00:52:39,400 --> 00:52:43,022
[SPEAKER_00]: and then the February Belinda event and just ran out of time.

557
00:52:44,403 --> 00:52:54,549
[SPEAKER_00]: So I met with Counselor Justin Steng on Zoom and we had a really good hour long brainstorming session of what this could be.

558
00:52:54,569 --> 00:53:03,394
[SPEAKER_00]: And then I went to the public library and I talked to the children's room librarian, Nicole Perreault.

559
00:53:03,455 --> 00:53:06,977
[SPEAKER_00]: I also met the assistant director, Sam Sednick.

560
00:53:07,737 --> 00:53:18,183
[SPEAKER_00]: They love the idea of us hosting an easy Chinese New Year or Lunar New Year event for the city and they're on board.

561
00:53:18,363 --> 00:53:28,608
[SPEAKER_00]: So Sam advised that we reserve the Bonsignor room ASAP on the actual day of the event, February 10th.

562
00:53:29,329 --> 00:53:35,832
[SPEAKER_00]: So we have the Bonsignor room, which is a beautiful room on the second floor reserved from 12 to 2.30.

563
00:53:37,573 --> 00:53:38,813
[SPEAKER_00]: on February 10th.

564
00:53:39,694 --> 00:53:49,356
