769
01:12:57,991 --> 01:13:13,886
[SPEAKER_03]: So I had emailed a copy of the Boston Human Rights Commission statement about the conflict in Gaza and Israel.

770
01:13:14,326 --> 01:13:14,546
[SPEAKER_03]: And I

771
01:13:18,950 --> 01:13:26,533
[SPEAKER_03]: was thinking, I know that probably I don't know, I mean, Adam made reference to it as well.

772
01:13:28,154 --> 01:13:42,679
[SPEAKER_03]: I was wondering if there was interest in discussing or trying to endorse a similar statement from the Medford Human Rights Commission regarding this conflict.

773
01:13:43,519 --> 01:13:43,860
[SPEAKER_03]: I can

774
01:13:45,701 --> 01:13:53,827
[SPEAKER_03]: I can either email or I'm not sure I can cut and paste the statement into the chat.

775
01:13:54,647 --> 01:14:00,451
[SPEAKER_03]: But that was my suggestion and I don't know what commissioners think of that idea.

776
01:14:01,723 --> 01:14:14,533
[SPEAKER_08]: So, Muneer, on our agenda, the writing of statements in support of or to denounce actions and situations, that's in the parking lot for January 2024.

777
01:14:14,633 --> 01:14:29,485
[SPEAKER_08]: That has to be discussed, yeah, with legal counsel present, because as a body that represents a city, we need to make sure that we understand all the parameters associated with that.

778
01:14:30,085 --> 01:14:32,447
[SPEAKER_08]: It's not the first time that it's come up.

779
01:14:32,587 --> 01:14:36,410
[SPEAKER_08]: It's not in regards to Israel Gaza.

780
01:14:36,550 --> 01:14:38,191
[SPEAKER_08]: It's just in general.

781
01:14:39,132 --> 01:14:44,916
[SPEAKER_08]: And I think that folks need to have the understanding before moving forward.

782
01:14:45,597 --> 01:14:52,662
[SPEAKER_08]: When we write these things we have to make sure that we're writing them from a place that is as non

783
01:14:53,062 --> 01:14:56,943
[SPEAKER_08]: personalize as possible on behalf of the city.

784
01:14:57,003 --> 01:15:04,644
[SPEAKER_08]: This is a human rights commission on behalf of the city enacted by ordinance.

785
01:15:04,924 --> 01:15:08,485
[SPEAKER_08]: That is the explanation that I received from legal.

786
01:15:08,605 --> 01:15:17,647
[SPEAKER_08]: So in January 2024, when legal is here, then I think that that would be the best time to have this conversation.

787
01:15:18,587 --> 01:15:21,468
[SPEAKER_08]: People, as individuals, you can

788
01:15:22,913 --> 01:15:25,637
[SPEAKER_08]: write your own statements, you can do whatever you want.

789
01:15:26,038 --> 01:15:33,287
[SPEAKER_08]: But as a member of the Human Rights Commission enacted by ordinance, we have to follow what is in law.

790
01:15:33,768 --> 01:15:38,535
[SPEAKER_08]: So in January, when legal is here, they can explain further.

791
01:15:39,684 --> 01:15:44,610
[SPEAKER_03]: So are you saying that the Human Rights Commission cannot issue statements without checking?

792
01:15:44,630 --> 01:15:51,018
[SPEAKER_08]: What I am saying is that in January, when legal is here, they can explain further.

793
01:15:51,178 --> 01:15:53,561
[SPEAKER_08]: I have given you what I was told.

794
01:15:53,681 --> 01:15:55,843
[SPEAKER_08]: That is why this is in the parking lot.

795
01:15:56,304 --> 01:16:07,991
[SPEAKER_08]: for January, but as individuals, as a person operating as an individual, you have the freedom to write whatever you want and say whatever you want.

796
01:16:08,131 --> 01:16:14,294
[SPEAKER_08]: But when we come together, we are together as a body representing a city.

797
01:16:15,755 --> 01:16:16,515
[SPEAKER_03]: Representing whom?

798
01:16:18,136 --> 01:16:18,477
[SPEAKER_08]: Sorry.

799
01:16:18,877 --> 01:16:21,018
[SPEAKER_08]: Representing the city of Medford.

800
01:16:21,078 --> 01:16:24,260
[SPEAKER_08]: We're the Human Rights Commission for the city of Medford.

801
01:16:24,992 --> 01:16:29,097
[SPEAKER_07]: So we're so this is yeah, this is a little confusing to me too.

802
01:16:29,217 --> 01:16:29,658
[SPEAKER_07]: So we're.

803
01:16:30,797 --> 01:16:36,400
[SPEAKER_07]: We're issuing something on behalf of the city, but wouldn't the mayor or somebody do that?

804
01:16:36,440 --> 01:16:44,403
[SPEAKER_08]: We're not issuing anything on behalf of the city, and that is why I'm asking legal to come in in January to discuss this.

805
01:16:44,683 --> 01:16:56,268
[SPEAKER_08]: If you remember, you asked about wanting to write statements in support of certain situations or against certain situations as the Human Rights Commission.

806
01:16:58,089 --> 01:17:01,310
[SPEAKER_07]: Actually, I brought that up, and that was not what I was trying.

807
01:17:01,390 --> 01:17:10,672
[SPEAKER_07]: I was trying to say, how do we discuss when people come to us and make a request?

808
01:17:10,812 --> 01:17:13,113
[SPEAKER_07]: Not so much how to.

809
01:17:13,353 --> 01:17:15,393
[SPEAKER_07]: So it got a little confused, I think.

810
01:17:15,893 --> 01:17:19,114
[SPEAKER_07]: They're kind of two separate things at the moment.

811
01:17:19,608 --> 01:17:23,351
[SPEAKER_07]: When the gentleman came last week, I'm sorry, Manur.

812
01:17:25,813 --> 01:17:28,154
[SPEAKER_07]: He was asking about a different topic.

813
01:17:28,374 --> 01:17:32,558
[SPEAKER_07]: And what I brought up was, how do we have that conversation?

814
01:17:32,638 --> 01:17:38,362
[SPEAKER_07]: Because I had, for example, questions from him about what we should consider or

815
01:17:39,251 --> 01:17:47,836
[SPEAKER_07]: And so somehow that got turned into just statements, which I think is- Please refer to the October meeting.

816
01:17:47,896 --> 01:17:49,537
[SPEAKER_08]: It was brought up in October.

817
01:17:49,557 --> 01:17:56,800
[SPEAKER_08]: If you remember, this is why we came up with the statement for, the broad statement for International Human Rights Day.

818
01:17:57,521 --> 01:18:02,824
[SPEAKER_08]: It was brought up in October about wanting to write statements in support of.

819
01:18:03,644 --> 01:18:05,265
[SPEAKER_08]: It was also discussed.

820
01:18:07,398 --> 01:18:14,460
[SPEAKER_08]: Again, when legal is here, I'm not going to define for you the parameters of what we can or what we can do.

821
01:18:14,480 --> 01:18:18,061
[SPEAKER_08]: I'm only gonna share the information that I have received.

822
01:18:18,501 --> 01:18:32,365
[SPEAKER_08]: When legal is here in January, you will have the opportunity to ask legal all the nuances that you can think of, and they will be the ones to advise on what we can or we cannot do.

823
01:18:34,730 --> 01:18:38,152
[SPEAKER_03]: Well, I okay, I will express my own personal opinion on that.

824
01:18:39,313 --> 01:18:49,938
[SPEAKER_03]: I think it is a shame that the Human Rights Commission cannot come up with a statement without checking with legal in the city.

825
01:18:50,538 --> 01:18:55,161
[SPEAKER_03]: If it's a human rights issue, I don't think legal has anything to do with it.

826
01:18:55,281 --> 01:18:57,022
[SPEAKER_03]: But that's my own personal opinion.

827
01:18:57,742 --> 01:19:17,674
[SPEAKER_03]: And I'm extremely disappointed that the Human Rights Commission cannot even discuss making such a statement in a matter that is very urgent, because it involves mass killings of people in that conflict.

828
01:19:18,755 --> 01:19:26,140
[SPEAKER_03]: And it is urgent that I think people have a chance to express their opinion, especially human rights commissions.

829
01:19:27,012 --> 01:19:29,953
[SPEAKER_03]: So that is my own personal opinion about that.

830
01:19:30,594 --> 01:19:37,837
[SPEAKER_03]: I'm happy also, if you'd like me to, I can contact the mayor and see what her opinion on the subject is.

831
01:19:38,297 --> 01:19:44,360
[SPEAKER_03]: But I somehow, as someone who has participated in the Human Rights Commission for

832
01:19:45,412 --> 01:19:50,438
[SPEAKER_03]: several years in the past, we have never had this problem before.

833
01:19:50,839 --> 01:20:01,172
[SPEAKER_03]: We were able to make statements that were related to human rights issues without discussing it either with the mayor or with legal counsel.

834
01:20:04,336 --> 01:20:06,898
[SPEAKER_07]: I have to agree, even though I don't understand.

835
01:20:06,958 --> 01:20:08,339
[SPEAKER_08]: Thank you for your opinion.

836
01:20:08,760 --> 01:20:16,206
[SPEAKER_08]: And I'm sorry, Maureen, but at this time, I'm actually going to close the subject and I'm going to explain why.

837
01:20:16,946 --> 01:20:30,558
[SPEAKER_08]: My understanding on Friday when I spoke to Attorney Austin about a variety of different things, not just this, is that we are tied into the ordinance for which we are created.

838
01:20:31,595 --> 01:20:43,366
[SPEAKER_08]: It just so happened to be that I mentioned what are our parameters and how can we write statements to show support of situations because people are asking.

839
01:20:43,867 --> 01:20:51,474
[SPEAKER_08]: So once again, I ask that you respect the fact that I'm barely bringing forward information and you wait until January.

840
01:20:51,994 --> 01:21:08,664
[SPEAKER_08]: when the attorney is here so that you can ask your questions directly to the attorney and you can get the clarification that you need from the attorney instead of taking what I say and determining that I have said that we can't write statements.

841
01:21:09,044 --> 01:21:10,625
[SPEAKER_08]: We must have clarity.

842
01:21:11,125 --> 01:21:13,887
[SPEAKER_08]: And in order to have clarity, we must have facts.

843
01:21:14,367 --> 01:21:18,069
[SPEAKER_08]: We must know what is our foundation of operation.

844
01:21:18,569 --> 01:21:19,550
[SPEAKER_08]: What are we doing?

845
01:21:21,668 --> 01:21:24,291
[SPEAKER_08]: This is not the first meeting that I've had.

846
01:21:24,692 --> 01:21:35,746
[SPEAKER_08]: I mean, there are many meetings that take place, not just on our commission, but even on the council floor, where open meeting laws and things of that nature are not respected.

847
01:21:36,707 --> 01:21:43,093
[SPEAKER_08]: I, for one, am somebody that does like to walk within the parameters of the law and to respect them.

848
01:21:43,534 --> 01:21:56,646
[SPEAKER_08]: So I ask for this clarity so that that way we don't find ourselves in a situation three or four months down the line because we wrote a statement and it was taken and it was used and we weren't legally entitled to.

849
01:21:58,488 --> 01:22:03,370
[SPEAKER_08]: So Munir, I welcome you to reach out to the mayor and to have a conversation with the mayor.

850
01:22:03,811 --> 01:22:10,734
[SPEAKER_08]: But you know, I defer to KP Law, who is currently in place of our legal counsel.

851
01:22:14,396 --> 01:22:18,498
[SPEAKER_03]: Okay, I completely disagree with this procedure.

852
01:22:19,178 --> 01:22:20,759
[SPEAKER_03]: I think it's passing the buck.

853
01:22:21,559 --> 01:22:23,020
[SPEAKER_03]: But so be it.

854
01:22:24,681 --> 01:22:26,802
[SPEAKER_03]: Thank you for even discussing it.

855
01:22:30,696 --> 01:22:31,096
[SPEAKER_08]: And we're at 656.

856
